 {"id":"franken_numpy-1xwh","title":"Match NumPy FFT Inf-component propagation","description":"The FFT adversarial harness shows Rust FFT outputs all NaN for input [1, Inf, 3, -Inf], while NumPy preserves infinite imaginary components for some coefficients. Investigate twiddle handling/special values and match NumPy's non-finite component behavior without regressing NaN propagation.","notes":"Fixed FFT Inf-component propagation to match NumPy. Added fft_mul() helper that treats near-zero twiddle factors (|x|<1e-14) as exactly zero when multiplied with Inf/NaN. All 1975 fnp-ufunc tests pass.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-18T12:08:39.451158855Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-18T12:22:56.111223792Z","closed_at":"2026-04-18T12:22:56.109447970Z","close_reason":"Completed by e9674ff: FFT Inf-component propagation now matches NumPy","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","fft","parity"]}
